# Playwright Test Style

## Locator Priority (inside page objects)

1. `getByRole`
2. `getByPlaceholder`
3. `getByText`
4. `getByTestId` only when needed for stability

Avoid CSS/XPath unless web-first locators are not reliable.

## Assertions

- Use web-first assertions: `toBeVisible`, `toHaveText`, `toHaveURL`, `toHaveCount`.
- Keep assertions explicit and deterministic (prefer exact text/count when possible).

## Timing and Stability

- Never use `page.waitForTimeout()`.
- Rely on Playwright auto-wait and assertion polling.

## Test Structure

- Prefer `test.step(...)` for readable scenario flow.
- Keep one clear outcome assertion per logical step (more if needed for guardrails).

## Examples

```ts
await test.step("Login and verify inventory", async () => {
  await loginPage.loginAs(SauceUser.STANDARD);
  await expect(page).toHaveURL(/inventory\.html$/);
});
```
